                <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 184.7/16b: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Commission to Negotiate Peace</gloss>
                        to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-07-10">July 10,
                            1919</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3053. Reports have reached the Commission that stories are being published in
                    America criticizing a dance recently given in the Hotel Crillon. On the night of
                    July 4th, as a part of the general celebration in Paris, the members of the
                    Staff of the Commission gave an informal dance, the first entertainment of any
                    kind by them since the beginning of the Conference. It was a subscription
                    affair, the expenses of which were borne by the guests themselves, and without
                    any cost whatever to the Government. The story should be denied.</p>
                <closer>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Am</hi>[<hi rend="smallcaps">erican</hi>] <hi
                        rend="smallcaps">Mission</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
